epresentation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Rysom was born in 1127, in Barnham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom, her father, John Rysam, was 27 and her mother, Mrs. John Rysom, was 22. She had at least 1 son with Sir Olenor Holme. She died in 1165, in her hometown, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1127–1165":"1127–1165","1124–1165":"1124–1165","1155–1196":"1155–1196","1100–Male":"1100–Surnud","1105–Female":"1105–Surnud","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1125":"1125","1124":"1124","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1165":"1165","1196":"1196","Barnham, Westhampnett, Sussex, England":"Barnham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barnham, West Hampnett, Sussex, England":"Barnham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Barnham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Barnham, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1127–1165":"1127–1165","1124–1165":"1124–1165","1155–1196":"1155–1196","1100–Male":"1100–Kuollut","1105–Female":"1105–Kuollut","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1125":"1125","1124":"1124","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1165":"1165","1196":"1196","Barnham, Westhampnett, Sussex, England":"Barnham, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barnham, West Hampnett, Sussex, England":"Barnham, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Barnham, Sussex, England, United Kingdom":"Barnham, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1127–1165":"1127–1165","1124–1165":"1124–1165","1155–1196":"1155–1196","1100–Male":"1100–Décédé","1105–Female":"1105–Décédée","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1125":"1125","1124":"1124","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1165":"1165","1196":"1196","Barnham, Westhampnett, Sussex, England":"Barnham, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Barnham, West Hampnett, Sussex, England":"Barnham, Sussex, Angle